    "summary": "I am a molecular microbiology researcher with ample living and working experience in Europe and Africa. I have done research on tropical and exotic diseases.like meningococcal epidemics in Africa, malaria, sleeping sickness , Lyme disease, Brucellosis.\nSince April 2015  I am Editor-in-Chief at DOAJ.   At DOAJ I am responsible for the global Ambassador programme which brings me to many countries of the world and end-responsible for managing of the Editorial Team of DOAJ.\nMy main research interests are: development of new assessment methods for scholarly publications,soil microbiota and the human microbiome, advocacy for open access and open science. I am strongly opposing the use of the Clarivate  ImpactFactor for the appraisal of scientific quality. Instead I think we should further develop article level metrics and open peer review. I am   working with Florence Piron (Quebec, Canada) and others on promoting global equity in science and publishing  with much emphasis on the situation in Africa and Latin America.\nMy main scientific expertise: medical research, project management, professional (NLP) communication skills, scientific information systems,  languages.\nRecent activities:  Instructor at Force11 summer school 2018 in San Diego (August 2018).. Lead of a group on Scholarly communication and inequity at the Triangle event in North Carolina (oct 2018) presenter at Predatory Journals Investigation Summit Ottawa, CN (2019)\nPrivately I am interested in sustainable building, ecology, health products. With my partner  I am working with a company called Ringana (ringana.com) on the promotion of fresh cosmetics, sports products and supplements. This Austrian company is unique because it provides fresh products in a market flooded with  with products containing chemicals that are damaging or even toxic for humans. Ringana is also  100% sustainable and working by ecological principles in all areas, from production processes to equal treatment of employees and suppliers to producing fresh, safe plant based products only. The company has an annual growth of 45% for the last 5 years and works through recommendation marketing with > 50.000 partners in many European countries. Anyone interested in the excellent job opportunities offered by Ringana or who wants to know more on the products  drop me a line and i will contact you with more information .",
